AT MIS TER. Preventative maintenance Isn't just a catch phrase. It's HOW we operate. It's the methodology that We're founded on and HOW We've been trained and have trained others for years. If NO ONE is performing preventative maintenance on your computers then NO ONE will notice when a hard drive begins to exhibit signs of failure then NO ONE will think to confirm whether or NOT the latest backup was successful. ‚Äã preventative maintenance is just AS important for computers and networks AS it is for automobiles, a mechanic CAN check and change a Car's fluids. Brakes and other items that tend to break down and likewise computer technicians should BE maintaining certain pArts of a computer and network system to help avoid potential disasters. Preventative maintenance Also helps establish performance benchmarks to USE in gauging degraded performance that helps identify hardware problems before they become failures. ‚Äã for businesses that aren't prepared to recover from a hardware or a data failure. It's often FAR worse and painstakingly more expensive to recover from. Regular backups are an integral part of ANY computer system and NOT having them in business is business suicide because It's NOT if something fails. It's when and unless it's tested regularly YOU won't know when components of your disaster recovery systems or strategy aren't actually working properly. Disaster recovery is different for every business but we recommend simplifying backup solutions and testing backup and restore systems and processes regularly.
